ClientResponses.Response: Hi, thank you very much for your feedback about the changes we've made! It's sad to hear you're not a fan of the new recipe but we appreciate your comments & will be passing them on to the rest of the team!

Results.ReviewText: Unfortunately the new 'Original' leaves a bitter taste instead of the smooth, rich coffee flavour we all loved. After being loyal Nescafe buyers for more years than we'd care to admit we now find ourselves looking for a replacement for the new 'Original'.  It is a real disappointment and we hope that Nescafe will 'wake up and smell the coffee beans' and bring back our favourite, true Original - it is sadly and greatly missed!
Results.Title: Change and not for the better

ClientResponses.Response:
We're really sorry to hear about your disappointment with the recent changes we've made to our Nescafé Original.

We worked on trying to make it a more enjoyable cup for you by developing some tech that in two steps helps to maintain the full flavour and aroma of our Nescafé Original, whilst taking out harsher and bitter compounds (Double Filter).

We've made a note of your comments & will be passing them on to the rest of the team.

When I was younger mum would always ask me to "flick the Kettle on love" as soon as she walked in from work.  Now I can't help but do the same and of course it has to be Nescafé Original every time
I've also learnt as I'm getting older myself that it has real benefits in a morning helping me focus for the day ahead - maybe I was still in bed when mum had a Nescafé in the mornings in them days

Results.ReviewText:
I love coffee, all coffee. From the exotic to the basic. But how do you compare the many different types? Nescafé Original - the Red Label.
This is my de facto standard for all other coffees. It is the ONLY coffee I have had at home for many years. When I am out and have a coffee I ask myself "is this is as good as Nescafé Original"? Rarely is the answer "yes".
Consistently good, consistently flavoursome and has a bite that wakes you up in the morning, yet relaxes you at night.
I cannot face the day without my mug of Nescafé.
Results.Title: Consistently top class

Results.ReviewText:
I am not a great coffee drinker so when I do drink it,it has to be the best! Nescafe Original is my first and only choice. Its tantalising  aroma when I unscrew the lid; its rich flavour: my taste buds are tempted before I add milk and sugar. The latter for me is needed for my coffee fix. I add soya milk because I love the taste. An extra creamy flavour follows when I add a little coconut oil to my coffee-drink.  This enhances the taste and my lips are always beautifully smooth. 
Nescafe Original: I wouldn't be without it!
